result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Adrienne L Frank was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Adrienne L Frank was found guilty of Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Adrienne L Frank in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 3:25 PM. State change of plea and will dismiss 16TR3. Resolution is defendant to plead G/NC to counts 1 & 2. Count 1 - 190 days in FC jail, fine of $3264, 30 month DL revocation and 30 month IID, $35 reimbursement to FC for blood draw, admission of 2 prior convictions. Count 2 - place on probation for 3 years with conditions of AODA, absolute sobriety, no possession, no entry into bars or taverns, FT employment, 200 hours community service, one NA/AA meeting per week - Counts 3 & 4 would be DRI and 5 would be dismissed out right. Court DRI counts 3 & 4 and dismisses Count 5 and 16TR03. DE pleads guilty to both counts 1 & 2. Court has PLQ and goes over it with the defendant, finds she is freely, voluntairly and intelligently entering her plea, waiving her constitutional rights and right to jury trial, court finds factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges guilty. Defendant admits to 2 prior OWI convictions. State make final statement and asks court to follow joint recommendation. Joy makes final statement and asks court to follow joint recommendation. Frank makes statement, remorseful. Court will accept joint recommendation and sentences the defendant to the following: Count 1 - 190 days in FC jail with huber, good time and also authorizes community service, must report to jail today, fine of $3,264 with 90 DTP/CO, 30 month DL revocation and 30 month IID - must not operate with out IID installed and must be installed in any vehicle registered or titled in her name and upon issuance of a valid license, $35 reimbursement to FC for blood draw. Count 2 - With hold sentence and place on probation for 3 years consecutive to the jail time in count 1 with conditions of AODA and follow through, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into bars or taverns, FT employment with job search report to DOC, 200 hours community service, one NA/AA meeting per week. Must submit DNA sample (expunction rights for DNA given), appeal, voting and firearm rights given. 5 days credit against the 190 day jail sentence.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 13, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
